<div class="card">
  <h2 class="section-title">Security Demonstration Dashboard</h2>
  <p class="info-text">
    This dashboard compares intentionally vulnerable error-handling routes with remediated secure routes.
  </p>
</div>

<div class="card demo-section-bad">
  <h3>Vulnerable Routes</h3>
  <p class="info-text">
    These routes intentionally expose exception messages, stack traces, and database details.
  </p>

  <div class="demo-links">
    <%= link_to "Missing Item Leak", leak_missing_item_path(9999), class: "bad-link" %>
    <%= link_to "Controller Error Leak", leak_controller_error_path, class: "bad-link" %>
    <%= link_to "Database Error Leak", leak_db_error_path, class: "bad-link" %>
  </div>
</div>

<div class="card demo-section-good">
  <h3>Secure Routes</h3>
  <p class="info-text">
    These routes handle the same error conditions safely and return generic user-facing responses.
  </p>

  <div class="demo-links">
    <%= link_to "Missing Item Secure", "/items/9999", class: "good-link" %>
    <%= link_to "Controller Error Secure", "/secure/controller_error", class: "good-link" %>
    <%= link_to "Database Error Secure", "/secure/db_error", class: "good-link" %>
  </div>
</div>